title: Melanella boscheineni
text:
Melanella boscheineni is a <a href="species">species</a> of <a href="sea%20snail">sea snail</a>, a <a href="marine%20%28ocean%29">marine</a> <a href="gastropod">gastropod</a> <a href="mollusk">mollusk</a> in the <a href="family%20%28biology%29">family</a> <a href="Eulimidae">Eulimidae</a>. The species is one of many species known to exist within the genus, "<a href="Melanella">Melanella</a>". This species is mainly distributed throughout <a href="Antarctic">Antarctic</a> waters.
Description.
The maximum recorded <a href="gastropod%20shell">shell</a> length is 5.2 mm.
Habitat.
Minimum recorded depth is 250 m. Maximum recorded depth is 305 m.
